HealthyLabs.AI Model & Retriever
Phase 1: The Data Contract (What the Colleague Needs to Know)
Before writing any retrieval logic, your colleague must understand exactly how the data
is formatted in Neo4j based on your pipeline's code.
1. The Vector Search Target (AtomicChunk) To do semantic search, the retriever must
target the AtomicChunk nodes.
• Target Property: a.embedding (This holds the BioLORD vector).
• Return Properties: a.content (the text), a.tier (1, 2, or 3),
a.authority_score (1.0, 0.7, 0.3), and a.document_id.
• Cypher Vector Search Example for Colleague:
Cypher
CALL db.index.vector.queryNodes('atomic_chunk_embedding', 5,
$query_embedding)
YIELD node AS a, score
MATCH (a)-[:PART_OF]->(c:ClinicalContext)-[:CHILD_OF]->(d:Document)
RETURN a.content AS text, a.authority_score AS authority, d.doc_uid
AS source_uid, score
2. The Hard Facts Target (The Knowledge Graph) To check for dosage limits or patient
history, the retriever must target the PRESCRIBED relationships created by
kg_service.py.
• Cypher Graph Query Example for Colleague:
Cypher
MATCH (d:Drug {name: $drug_name})-[r:PRESCRIBED]->(p:Patient {id:
$patient_id})
RETURN r.dosage AS dosage, r.frequency AS frequency, r.unit AS unit,
r.authority
