1. The Updated API Contract (What the Frontend Sends)
Your colleague needs to update api/request_models.py to expect a rich, structured
patient_context object alongside the query.
Give this exact JSON payload to your frontend team and your backend colleague:
JSON
{
 "query_text": "Can I take ibuprofen for my headache?",
 "session_id": "uuid-1234",
 "patient_context": {
 "age": 65,
 "gender": "male",
 "current_medications": [
 {"name": "Lisinopril", "dosage": "10mg", "frequency":
"daily"},
 {"name": "Metformin", "dosage": "500mg", "frequency": "twice
